ment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn89074274/1921-02-10/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/ndhi/batch_ndhi_kensal_ver01/data/sn89074274/00212475932/1921021001/0057.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn89074274/1921-02-10/ed-1/?sp=8"], "batch": ["ndhi_kensal_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/north dakota/", "2/united states/north dakota/barnes/", "3/united states/north dakota/barnes/valley city/"], "contributor": ["state historical society of north dakota"], "date": "1921-02-10", "dates": ["1921-02-10"], "description": ["AGE EIGHT From Wednesdays Daily The interior of the Right Price store is being repainted at the pres ent time C 0 Langer the Sanborn merchant was looking after business matters in the city last night Mrs Vernon Gale entertained Miss Emma DeWitt and Clara L Larson at dinner Monday Attorney C S Buck of Jamestown N D was looking after legal busi ness in the city last night Today marks the beginning of the Lenten season Today is known as Ash Wednesday Mr and Mrs Bob Rathje of Tower City were in the city Tuesday and remained over to attend the organ recital at the Congregational church Herb Weston arrived in the city this morning from the farm near Sheldon and will spend a few days in the city Herman Cook and his mother who have been at Long Beach California for the past month or two returned to Valley City Monday of this week A McPaul wire chief of the local telephone exchange will go to Fargo this evening to attend a meeting of the company A few automobile drivers in the city have secured the 1921 licenses The licenses have a blue background and white numerals Kermit"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-25T19:29:06.422Z", "group": ["ndnp/ndhi", "state-histrorical-society-of-north-dakota-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://w